AMC Networks Gains After Second-Quarter Sales Beat Estimates

-- B y   V i l l e   H e i s k a n e n
-- 
2011-08-11T20:28:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-11/amc-networks-gains-after-second-quarter-sales-exceed-analysts-estimates.html
AMC Networks Inc., the cable-network
operator that airs “Mad Men” and “Breaking Bad,” had its biggest
gain in Nasdaq trading since its June spinoff from  Cablevision
Systems Corp. (CVC)  after sales beat analysts’ estimates.  AMC rose $4.03, or 13 percent, to $34.31 at 4 p.m. New York
time on the Nasdaq Stock Market. The stock is still down 21
percent since the June 30 spinoff.  Second-quarter sales climbed 12 percent to $292 million.
Analysts predicted $283.4 million, the average of estimates
compiled by Bloomberg. Net income rose to $27.2 million from
$22.1 million.  The New York-based company, formerly known as Rainbow
Media, owns television channels IFC, WE tv, Sundance Channel and
AMC, which airs the Emmy-award winning “Mad Men” about the
1960s New York advertising industry.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ville Heiskanen in New York at 
